# ClearPass Certificate Manager – crontab for supercronic
#
# supercronic notes:
#   - Does not use or require SHELL= directive
#   - Runs each job directly without a shell wrapper; scripts must be executable
#   - Job output goes to supercronic's stdout/stderr (visible in docker compose logs)
#   - Timezone is controlled by the TZ environment variable in the container
#
# acme.sh only renews when ≤30 days remain on the certificate.
# On successful renewal, install_cert.sh copies flat files and uploads to ClearPass.

# Run renewal check at 02:00 and 14:00 container-local time every day
0 2  * * * /opt/cppm/renew.sh
0 14 * * * /opt/cppm/renew.sh
